  <mainContent><![CDATA[<h2>Course Overview</h2>
<p>This programme offers students the opportunity to progress from a Foundation Degree in Early Years and gain a full BA (Hons) degree.</p>
<h2>Entry Requirements</h2>
<ul>
<li>A Foundation Degree (or equivalent) in Early Years</li>
<li>GCSE Grade C or above in English and Maths.</li>
</ul>
<p>All applicants will be interviewed.</p>
<h2>What will I study? </h2>
<p>This BA (Hons) programme aims to develop students personally, professionally and academically, enhancing their ability to think critically about Early Years education.</p>
<p>It is designed to recruit students from a diverse range of backgrounds, who have an interest in Early Years education. Students will be able to make the links between education policy, its delivery and the experience of groups and individuals.</p>
<p>This course is offered in partnership with, and validated by, University of Hertfordshire.</p>]]></mainContent>
